<br>
Perhaps a little analogy will clear things up.  I have a friend. His name is Fred. He is 40 years old.  He works 9 to 5, pays his taxes.  Has never beat up anyone, stolen from anyone, driven drunk or downloaded an mp3.  Fred buys some marijuana and has a few joints on a Friday night in the privacy of his own home.  Say the cops get a tip, catch him, throw him in jail.  Thanks to 'zero tolerance' laws hes now doing 5 years and has lost the right to vote for life.  Now expain to me who's been victimized here?  Who did Fred hurt?  Who did Fred hurt *enough* to justify such a harsh sentence?<br>
<br>
<br>
I would quite happily throw away the key if he willingly drank himseful stupid and jumped in a car...if he willingly broke into someones house and stole their possessions.  But I dont' see how hes hurt *anyone* other than himself by sitting alone in his room enjoying some marijuana.<br>
