<br>
&quot;To slow it down, marijuana would have a negligable &quot;relative value&quot;, since the good is only benefiting the individual. An example of something that would be the &quot;greater good for the greatest number&quot;, would be to harvest food, or build a large communal building for all to use.&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
I look at it in terms of cost/benefit.  Example. I am quite anti-booze. Hate the stuff.  But I realise that if prohibition was still in effect, crime would most likely be even more *out of control* and society would have a bigger problem on it's hands than if it decided to regulate it. Prohibtion leads to black market leads to murders leads to gang wars leads to exorbitant costs of enforcing leads to otherwise non-violent people going to jail leads to costing taxpayers a hell of a lot of money.<br>
<br>
